{"author":{"id":"b78c39e7b13f90a5827abfba043255fe7a4ede1499df23f110fffe5abfa44adc"},"ops":[{"type":1,"timestamp":1770138059,"nonce":"Ov98uus/b5vQ2xG7/KhkVUuwtG4=","metadata":{"github-id":"I_kwDOQ241x87n_v-y","github-url":"https://github.com/rolker/ros2_agent_workspace/issues/151","origin":"github"},"title":"Add git notes for agent handoff audit trail","message":"## Summary\n\nImplement git notes workflow for preserving rich context during agent handoffs, inspired by Conductor's audit trail approach.\n\n## Parent Issue\n\nSub-issue of #139\n\n## Motivation\n\nConductor uses `git notes` to attach detailed summaries to commits:\n- Task completion summaries with context\n- Phase checkpoint verification results\n- Handoff notes between sessions\n\nBenefits of git notes:\n- **Searchable**: `git log --notes` shows all notes\n- **Non-intrusive**: Doesn't clutter commit messages\n- **Preservable**: Can be pushed/pulled separately\n- **Rich context**: Unlimited length, markdown supported\n\n## Current State\n\nOur workspace relies on:\n- Commit messages (limited, terse)\n- PR descriptions (lost after merge for quick reference)\n- Issue comments (requires GitHub access)\n\n## Proposed Solution\n\n### Handoff Note Script\n\n**File**: `.agent/scripts/add_handoff_note.sh`\n\n```bash\n# Add a handoff note to the current or specified commit\n#\n# Usage: \n#   add_handoff_note.sh                    # Interactive, current commit\n#   add_handoff_note.sh --commit \u003csha\u003e     # Specific commit\n#   add_handoff_note.sh --message \"...\"   # Non-interactive\n```\n\n### Note Template\n\n```markdown\n## Agent Handoff Note\n\n**Agent**: Copilot CLI Agent (Claude Opus 4.5)\n**Timestamp**: 2026-02-03T16:54:00Z\n**Issue**: #139\n\n### What Was Done\n- Implemented feature X\n- Updated tests for Y\n\n### Current State\n- All tests passing\n- Ready for Phase 2\n\n### Next Steps\n- Implement Phase 2 tasks\n- Review with user before proceeding\n\n### Blockers/Notes\n- None\n```\n\n### View Notes Script\n\n**File**: `.agent/scripts/view_handoff_notes.sh`\n\n```bash\n# View handoff notes for recent commits or specific issue\n#\n# Usage:\n#   view_handoff_notes.sh                  # Last 10 commits with notes\n#   view_handoff_notes.sh --issue 139      # Notes for issue #139 commits\n```\n\n## Tasks\n\n- [ ] Create `add_handoff_note.sh` script\n- [ ] Create note template\n- [ ] Create `view_handoff_notes.sh` script\n- [ ] Document in CLI_COMMANDS.md\n- [ ] Add to agent session end workflow (suggestion, not required)\n- [ ] Document how to push/pull notes: `git push origin refs/notes/*`\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n\n- [ ] Can add structured notes to commits\n- [ ] Can view notes for issue-related commits\n- [ ] Notes survive push/pull when configured\n- [ ] Works with all agent frameworks\n- [ ] Non-intrusive (optional enhancement, not required)\n\n## Effort Estimate\n\n**Small** (2-3 hours)\n\n## Priority\n\n**Low** - Enhancement for complex multi-session work\n\n## References\n\n- [Git Notes documentation](https://git-scm.com/docs/git-notes)\n- Conductor workflow.md \"Attach Task Summary with Git Notes\" section\n\n---\n**🤖 Authored-By**: `Copilot CLI Agent`\n**🧠 Model**: `Claude Opus 4.5`","files":null}]}